      <div class="m-auto w-full sm:w-2/3 xl:w-1/2 mb-16 px-8" id="english">
        <p class="mb-6">Complaint Process</p>
        <ol class="list-decimal pl-4">
          <li>
            <p class="mb-6">Individuals who feel they have not been treated fairly complete a “<a class="text-secondary-500"
                href="https://forms.gle/zY6MJz9s7SCnJpZ67"><u>Complaint Form</u></a>” in writing or through an online portal.
              Form should be completed within 14 working days after the event or action that is the basis for the
              Complaint.&nbsp;</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="mb-6">Complaint Form is directed to ECSH Program Director<i> </i>and ORR Supervisor. Program Director
              and ORR Supervisor meet promptly and usually within three days to discuss and document the complaint and
              response. If the Program Director or ORR Supervisor is included in the complaint, they will not participate in
              this process. Additional staff may be included in this meeting if needed.&nbsp;</p>
            <ol class="list-decimal pl-4">
              <li>
                <p class="mb-6">Documentation should include:&nbsp;</p>
                <ol class="list-decimal pl-4">
                  <li>
                    <p class="mb-6">Date,&nbsp;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p class="mb-6">Requested Service,&nbsp;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p class="mb-6">Evidence of ORR Eligibility of the individual,&nbsp;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p class="mb-6">Documentation of the conversation or interaction leading to the complaint.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p class="mb-6">Two staff members chosen to meet with the individual and interpreter if needed. Staff
                      members will be chosen based on gender, ethnicity, language, or other essential factors.</p>
                  </li>
                </ol>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="mb-6">Two members of staff promptly and within three days contact the individual to meet and discuss the
              circumstances of the complaint. An interpreter who is not involved with the case will assist the individual.
              Meeting may include requesting evidence of ORR eligibility or additional information related to the
              circumstances of the complaint.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="mb-6">The Program Director and ORR Supervisor will promptly and usually within 7 working days review all
              documentation of all the actions taken to-date and will make an attempt to resolve the situation.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="mb-6">The decision and outcome of the complaint will be immediately shared with the individual based on
              the method (email, phone, mail, in person, etc) recorded in the complaint and will be included in the
              documentation.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
        <p class="mb-6">Formal Appeal Process</p>
        <ol class="list-decimal pl-4">
          <li>
            <p class="mb-6">If the complaint is not resolved to the individual’s satisfaction, the individual may submit the
              complaint and any supporting documentation to the Afghan Partner’s Board by email or mail to ______.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="mb-6">The Afghan Partner Board of Directors will meet promptly to hear the individual’s complaint. An
              Interpreter who is not involved with the case will assist the client. Under most circumstances, the meeting
              shall be within 30 working days of receipt of the request for an appeal. The Afghan Partner Board of Directors
              will promptly furnish its findings to the Program Director and the individual.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
        <p class="mb-6">The complaint process and record of its activity is confidential</p>
